 # Changelog
 
+## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S2-P03-T028 (DuckDB independent open-history verification; NOT_DEPLOYED)
+
+- Twenty-eighth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S2-P03), one task per run. Goal: independently verify the open history with DuckDB so the recovery and analysis path is not locked to a single Cloudflare Beta capability. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; an offline verifier reads the T027 open Parquet snapshot with DuckDB -- a different engine from the pyarrow writer -- via read_parquet over local files, with NO R2 SQL and NO R2 Data Catalog and no Cloudflare. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: tools/duckdb_verify.py plus evidence/ADP-S2-P03-T028/{rebuild_report.json, sample_queries.sql}. Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S2-P03-T028/test-results/duckdb_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): materializing the full 92-partition snapshot from the committed T027 logical tables and rebuilding with DuckDB yields 498 documents, 500 versions, 46 months (2016-01 to 2026-07), zero orphan version rows, per-month version-creation events that match the logical ground truth exactly, and the derivable signals (repost/multi-source, multi-version, status distribution) -- and every count cross-checks against the committed T027 manifest and logical tables, proving the key documents, versions, events, and signals rebuild from the open format alone with no vendor Beta. The independent rebuild also surfaced a descriptive errata: T027 wrote the month-range end as 2025-10, whereas the true maximum month is 2026-07 (the 46-month count and all data and hashes were always correct); this commit corrects the T027 evidence and spec docs and the T027 CHANGELOG line, while the append-only T027 event is left immutable and this errata records the fix. A dev dependency duckdb==1.1.3 was installed into the user's Python 3.9 user-site as the offline independent engine; the runtime and worker do not use it. Cost (unknown != 0): new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-16 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S2-P03-T027 (monthly open-format snapshot + manifest; NOT_DEPLOYED)
 
-- Twenty-seventh task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program and the first of S2-P03 (open snapshots, recovery, and orchestration cost), one task per run. Goal: export the canonical documents and their append-only version chains as a monthly-partitioned open columnar snapshot (real Apache Parquet) plus a hashed manifest, for large-scale historical analysis, recovery, and backtestable prediction. NOT_DEPLOYED, 0 recurring cloud cost; the snapshot is generated offline from a D1 sample and touches no production D1, R2, or worker. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/: tools/snapshot_writer.py (derives two typed logical tables -- cn_documents and cn_document_versions -- from a D1 sample via the T024 canonicalizer and the T026 version engine, partitions each by month, writes real Parquet via pyarrow with a deterministic NDJSON fallback, carries a versioned SCHEMA_REGISTRY with a backward-compatible evolve_schema, and emits a snapshot_manifest), SNAPSHOT_SPEC.md, and schemas/snapshot_manifest.schema.json. Reproducibility is anchored on a format- and engine-independent logical_hash (a Parquet stream embeds the writer version, so physical bytes only match within one engine version); the manifest records both the logical_hash and the physical_sha256. Acceptance verified over the real 500-item D1 sample (evidence/ADP-S2-P03-T027/test-results/snapshot_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): the snapshot is 498 canonical documents / 500 versions / 46 months (2016-01..2025-10) / 92 partitions; the same logical snapshot regenerates identically (equal snapshot_id, equal per-partition logical_hash, and equal physical Parquet bytes in-environment); the D1 sample and the Parquet are row- and relationship-consistent (498 document rows and 500 version rows read back from Parquet match the sample-derived tables, every version's canonical_id resolves to a document with zero orphans, and every row lands in the correct month partition); and schema evolution is backward compatible (adding a nullable column lets an old v1 partition still read with the new column null-filled while the v1 logical_hash stays stable). The committed logical_snapshot/*.jsonl recomputes all 92 manifest logical_hashes offline without pyarrow, and the manifest validates against its draft-07 schema. A dev dependency pyarrow==17.0.0 was installed into the user's Python 3.9 user-site to emit real Parquet; it is an offline evidence dependency the runtime/worker do not use, and the writer falls back to deterministic NDJSON with the identical logical_hash when it is absent. Cost (unknown != 0): new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
